This paper deals with reinforcement learning and optimal control of Markov decision processes, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. The paper also discusses actor-critic architectures, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems (cs.RO and cs.SY). The use of f-divergences and their relationship to information theory suggests a potential fit for the data structures and algorithms category (cs.DS). Overall, the most likely categories are those related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI).
